video.title: Garfunkel and Oates
video.synopsis: Two hapless, twentysomething single women try to make it as a duo performing satirical songs about their personal and professional lives.

episodes.synopsis: Riki dates a fellow comedian, while Kate looks for a discreet way to end a relationship and auditions for a movie role outside her comfort zone.
episodes.title: The Fadeaway

episodes.synopsis: Riki and Kate discover their musical act has inspired a pornographic imitation -- Garfinger and Butts -- and a corporate gig goes wrong.
episodes.title: Rule 34

episodes.synopsis: After noticing that men are attracted to women who barely talk, Riki and Kate decide to perform a social experiment on their next double date.
episodes.title: Speechless

episodes.synopsis: When Riki and Kate put on their 1,000th show together, an insistent heckler, a difficult audio tech and more almost wreck their performance.
episodes.title: Road Warriors

episodes.synopsis: Curious to know if the world really treats blondes and brunettes differently, Riki and Kate change into wigs of opposite shades.
episodes.title: Hair Swap

episodes.synopsis: A bitter ex-bandmate who is now a movie star takes revenge on Riki and Kate, and the women celebrate their "bandaversay" by getting weed cards.
episodes.title: Third Member

episodes.synopsis: After attending a baby sprinkle, Riki visits a fertility doctor. When Kate learns she has "Peter Pan Syndrome" she questions her direction in life.
episodes.title: Eggs

episodes.synopsis: Riki tries to hook up with an ex when fertility drugs boost her libido, and Kate dates a guy on her emotional maturity level -- a high school boy.
episodes.title: Maturity
